text:
This coffeeshop is super run down, it's old and dark. The toilet isn't well kept.
But the Indian food there is reasonably okay.
The tzechar is tasty. Hidden gem in a quiet neighborhood.
Superb coffee from the drink stall. Thank to my favourite Âßê customised the to my preference. Plus the sio sio nasi lemak. Power la dey! Haha.

The mixed rice keeping the same price of $2.50 of regular 2 Veg and 1 meat. There will be left over at night if you want.

Zhi Char is quite awesome compare to others neighborhood. Curry chicken rice is quite thick.

A small coffee shop with 4 stalls only but the foods are comparable to food centre. Prata and bryani nice are good, mixed-vege rice has many dishes, wanton noodle and chicken rice are also nice üòÄüôÉ.
